# Fixing PHP deprecation warnings

FreeCRM runs on PHP 8.3. Deprecations are routed through `WebUI_ErrorHandler` ‚Üí `cache/logs/system.log` as `[warning][php]`. Fix them at the source; do not suppress with `@` or lower `EXCEPTION_ERROR_LEVEL`.

See also: `error-checking.mdc` (where to look), `php-coding-standards.mdc` (typing/style).

## 1. Creation of dynamic property ‚Ä¶ is deprecated

**Cause:** PHP 8.2 forbids assigning undeclared object properties (`$obj->foo = ‚Ä¶`).

**Fix:** Declare the property on the class that receives the assignment. Match visibility to how callers/templates access it (Smarty often needs `public`).

```php
// src/Modules/Base/Models/Record.php
public array $colorList = [];

// src/Modules/Base/Models/Link.php
public $linkKey;
public $related;
public $countRelated;
```

**Where to look:**
- Stack trace class + property name.
- Grep the property name to find all assignment sites.
- Common targets: `App\Modules\Base\Models\Link`, `Record`, adapters under `src/ModuleManagement/Adapters/`.
- `Link::initialize()` and `Link::getInstanceFromValues()` assign every key from value maps ‚Äî declare all keys used in link arrays and `.tpl` files (`$LINK->get('‚Ä¶')`, `$LISTVIEW_ENTRY->‚Ä¶`).
- `Views/Pagination.php` that cache `$listViewEntries` / `$listViewCount` but extend `Index` or `IndexAjax` (not `ListView`) ‚Äî copy property declarations from the module‚Äôs `ListView.php`.
- **Utility modules not extending `CRMEntity`** (`ModTracker`, `OpenStreetMap`, `Password`, ‚Ä¶): `CRMEntity::getInstance()` always sets `$focus->moduleName = $module` ‚Äî declare `public $moduleName;` on the module class.

**Do not:** add `#[\AllowDynamicProperties]` or leave properties undeclared ‚Äúfor flexibility‚Äù.

## 2. Automatic conversion of false to array is deprecated

**Cause:** A property initialized as `false` is later used with array syntax (`$prop[$key] = ‚Ä¶`).

**Fix:** Initialize as an empty typed array.

```php
// Before
private $fieldsInHeader = false;

// After
private array $fieldsInHeader = [];
```

Smarty `{if $VAR}` treats `[]` as falsy ‚Äî no template change needed.

## 3. filemtime(): stat failed for libraries/‚Ä¶

**Cause:** `vresource_url()` in `src/Runtime/TemplateHelpers.php` probed web-relative paths as filesystem paths. Static assets live only under `public/` (document root).

**Fix:** Resolve cache-busting mtime only via `ROOT_DIRECTORY/public/‚Ä¶`. Check `is_file()` before `filemtime()`. Do not probe the bare URL or project root without `public/`.

```php
$path = ROOT_DIRECTORY . DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR . 'public' . DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR . ltrim($url, '/');
if (is_file($path)) {
    return $url . '?s=' . filemtime($path);
}
```

**Note:** `@filemtime()` does not suppress warnings inside the called function on PHP 8+ when a custom error handler is registered.

## 4. Smarty: unregistered static method ‚Ä¶ is deprecated

**Cause:** Smarty 4 requires explicit class registration before templates call `\Fully\Qualified\Class::method()`.

**Preferred fix (controller-first):** move the call to PHP and pass a variable ‚Äî do not add `registerClass()` for new code.

| Call site | Where to prepare data |
|-----------|----------------------|
| Widget `.tpl` | Widget class `getWidget()` ‚Üí enrich `$this->Config['data']` |
| View `.tpl` | View `process()` / `preProcess()` ‚Üí `$viewer->assign()` |
| UiType `.tpl` | UiType instance method ‚Üí `$FIELD_MODEL->getUITypeModel()->‚Ä¶()` |
| Global chrome | `BaseViewController::getViewer()` or module view |

**Fallback:** register in `src/Runtime/CRM_Viewer.php` ‚Üí `registerSmartyPlugins()` only when refactor is out of scope.

**After moving calls out of templates:** grep `layouts/**/*.tpl` for the class; remove dead `registerClass()` entries (e.g. `vtlib\Functions`, short aliases like bare `CurrencyField` when only `\App\Fields\CurrencyField` remains). Duplicate registrations (`AppConfig` + `\App\Core\AppConfig`) stay until all templates use one form.

**Where to look:**
- Log message names the class + method; grep that class in `layouts/**/*.tpl`.
- After fix: `rm -f cache/templates_c/*.php` and reload the page.

## Workflow

1. Reproduce via browser (not CLI-only) and read `cache/logs/system.log`.
2. Identify pattern from message (dynamic property / false‚Üíarray / stat failed).
3. Apply the matching fix above ‚Äî minimal diff, no compat shims.
4. Reload the page; confirm the warning is gone and behaviour unchanged.

## Quick grep helpers

```bash
rg "->colorList" src/
rg "getInstanceFromValues" src/ --glob '*.php'
rg "vresource_url" layouts/ src/
rg "listViewEntries|listViewCount" src/ --glob '**/Views/Pagination.php'
rg "\\\\App\\\\" layouts/ --glob '*.tpl'   # Smarty static calls ‚Äî refactor or registerClass
rg "registerClass\(" src/Runtime/CRM_Viewer.php   # audit dead registrations after tpl refactor
rg "Kandydaci|fieldmodulerel" migrations/ bin/   # module-rename leftovers
```
